{"type":"message","id":"e42e5a20","parentId":"25355404","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:00:46.399Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Investigating Document Synthesis**\n\nI'm currently focused on how to construct the `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` content. I've realized I need to synthesize the information, since source files are missing. The prompts will serve as a core guide, alongside my understanding of HFT bot systems. I'm considering other information sources.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Master Protocol**\n\nI'm now drafting `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`, focusing on synthesizing information from the prompts, as the source documents are absent. I'm prioritizing the core sections mentioned, such as SACS-2026 and Atomic Rollback. Then, I will address `src/agent_wrapper.py`, which I will create, focusing on its ability to manage `/start_bot`, `/stop_bot`, and `/status`. Finally, I'll document my model optimization strategy.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771156846394_532","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md","content":"# MASTER PROTOCOL (Supreme Law)\n\n**Version:** 1.0.0  \n**Status:** ACTIVE  \n**Enforcement:** MANDATORY  \n**Authority:** PRO STREAM\n\n---\n\n## 1. PREAMBLE\nThis Master Protocol serves as the immutable \"Supreme Law\" for the OpenClaw Trading Automation System. All agents, sub-agents, and human operators must adhere to these directives. No code shall be deployed, no trade executed, and no system modified in violation of these tenets.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SACS-2026 (System Availability & Continuity Standard)\n**Objective:** Guarantee 99.99% uptime for core trading loops.\n\n*   **Fleet Integrity:** All 12 core agents (QUANT, NET, SENTINEL, OPS, DB, LOG, DMARKET, STEAM, HYPE, INVENTORY, SEC, LOGIC) must be active.\n*   **Heartbeat Protocol:** Every component must emit a heartbeat every 30 seconds. Three missed heartbeats trigger an automatic restart sequence.\n*   **Redundancy:** Critical paths (Price Feed, Order Execution) must have N+1 failover redundancy.\n\n## 3. ATOMIC ROLLBACK PROTOCOL\n**Objective:** Zero undefined states.\n\n*   **Definition:** Every deployment or configuration change is a transaction.\n*   **The Rule of Two:**\n    1.  **Pre-Flight Snapshot:** No change proceeds without a verified system snapshot.\n    2.  **Verification Gate:** Post-deployment validation must pass 100% of critical tests within 60 seconds.\n*   **Failure Response:** If Verification Gate fails, the system must *automatically* and *atomically* revert to the Pre-Flight Snapshot. No manual intervention required for safety restoration.\n\n## 4. SPEC-FIRST DEVELOPMENT\n**Objective:** Documentation leads implementation.\n\n*   **Workflow:**\n    1.  **Draft:** Create/Update the Markdown specification (e.g., `docs_archive/FEATURE.md`).\n    2.  **Review:** Validate the spec against the Master Protocol.\n    3.  **Code:** Implement strictly according to the approved spec.\n    4.  **Verify:** Tests must trace back to specific lines in the spec.\n*   **Prohibition:** \"Cowboy coding\" (implementation without documentation) is strictly forbidden.\n\n## 5. OBSERVABILITY & METRICS\n**Objective:** Total visibility, zero blind spots.\n\n*   **Logging:** JSON-structured logs are mandatory for all machine-readable events.\n*   **Metrics:**\n    *   **Latency:** Tracking of `tick-to-trade` latency at p50, p99, and p99.9.\n    *   **Error Rate:** Alert threshold at >1% error rate on any API interface.\n    *   **P&L:** Real-time tracking of Profit & Loss per strategy and aggregate.\n*   **Dashboards:** Monitoring states must be accessible via CLI (`/status`) and visual dashboards.\n\n## 6. HFT RULES (High-Frequency Trading)\n**Objective:** Speed with safety.\n\n*   **Risk Limits:**\n    *   **Max Drawdown:** Hard stop at 2% daily drawdown.\n    *   **Position Sizing:** No single position > 5% of total capital.\n    *   **Kill Switch:** A global hardware/software kill switch must be available to terminate all active orders in < 100ms.\n*   **Execution:**\n    *   **Maker/Taker:** Prefer Maker orders to capture rebate/spread unless high-urgency Taker liquidity is required.\n    *   **Inventory:** maintain neutral inventory exposure where possible (delta neutral strategies).\n\n---\n\n## 7. MODEL OPTIMIZATION STRATEGY\n**Objective:** Leverage AI model strengths for specific roles.\n\n### 7.1. Architect/Trader (Gemini 3 Pro)\n*   **Role:** Complex pattern recognition, strategy formulation, market analysis.\n*   **Context:** 1M+ token window for full historical price data analysis.\n*   **Configuration:**\n    *   `Temperature`: 0.7 (Balanced Creativity)\n    *   `Top_P`: 0.95\n*   **Usage:** Weekly strategy reviews, code architecture, anomaly investigation.\n\n### 7.2. Validator/Signal (Gemini 3 Flash)\n*   **Role:** High-speed syntax checking, trade signature validation, safety guardrails.\n*   **Configuration:**\n    *   `Temperature`: 0.0 (Strict Deterministic)\n    *   `Top_P`: 0.1\n*   **Usage:** Pre-trade checks, continuous integration pipelines, log parsing.\n\n---\n*Signed: SYSTEM ORCHESTRATOR*\n"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":6498,"output":1444,"cacheRead":5072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":7942,"cost":{"input":0.012995999999999999,"output":0.017328,"cacheRead":0.0010144000000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.031338399999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771156830431}}
