{"type":"message","id":"191fbe0f","parentId":"b2652fd2","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:01:01.218Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Simulating the Bot**\n\nI'm currently focused on the `src/main.py` placeholder. I'm building a barebones implementation that mimics a running bot, complete with log printing and sleep functions. This will allow `agent_wrapper.py` to interact with it as intended. This dummy bot will get the ball rolling, until a real bot is available.\n\n\n**Building the Dummy Bot**\n\nNow I'm creating `src/main.py`. It's a simple simulation: prints logs and sleeps. This sets the stage for `agent_wrapper.py`. I'll get that controller script running next, using `argparse` to handle the commands like `start`, `stop`, and `status`. I'll treat the commands as strings.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771156861206_534","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import time\nimport sys\nimport os\n\ndef main():\n    print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] BOT STARTED. PID: {os.getpid()}\")\n    sys.stdout.flush()\n    try:\n        while True:\n            print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] Bot running... monitoring markets.\")\n            sys.stdout.flush()\n            time.sleep(5)\n    except KeyboardInterrupt:\n        print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] BOT STOPPING...\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] BOT CRASHED: {e}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n","file_path":"src/main.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":7990,"output":375,"cacheRead":5314,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8365,"cost":{"input":0.015979999999999998,"output":0.0045000000000000005,"cacheRead":0.0010628,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.021542799999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771156853123}}
