{"type":"message","id":"672f2117","parentId":"4a389aef","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:01:17.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Building the Agent Wrapper**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm currently focused on the `src/agent_wrapper.py` script. The immediate goal is to establish argument parsing, focusing on 'start', 'stop', and 'status' flags. The 'start' function needs robust PID file management and should launch `src/main.py` using `subprocess.Popen` if the agent isn't already running. I will also save the PID to the `bot.pid` file.\n\n\n**Refining Argument Handling**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI've begun implementation of the argument parsing in `src/agent_wrapper.py`. I'm using `argparse` to handle 'start', 'stop', and 'status' flags. The 'start' function now includes PID file checks and will use `subprocess.Popen` to launch `src/main.py`. I'm placing the `bot.pid` file in the `src/` directory for better organization. I will also incorporate Windows-specific process management, potentially using `os.kill` or `taskkill`.\n\n\n**Structuring Agent Logic**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm now fully focused on the structure of `src/agent_wrapper.py`. I've outlined the argument parsing using `argparse` and have begun work on the 'start', 'stop', and 'status' functions. The 'start' function will utilize `subprocess.Popen` to launch `src/main.py`. I'll place the PID file, `bot.pid`, in the `src/` directory. To ensure cross-platform compatibility, I will use `os.kill` for process management, and Windows specific commands if required. I've decided to avoid additional dependencies like `psutil`. I'm starting to consider how to handle Windows process termination using `taskkill` or the process object's `terminate()` method.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771156877080_535","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import sys\nimport os\nimport subprocess\nimport argparse\nimport signal\nimport time\n\nPID_FILE = \"src/bot.pid\"\nBOT_SCRIPT = \"src/main.py\"\n\ndef is_running(pid):\n    \"\"\"Check if a process with the given PID is running.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        # Windows-specific check could be added here, but signal 0 is widely supported for existence check\n        # On Windows, os.kill with 0 is not supported in older versions, but usually fine in modern Python.\n        # Alternative: use tasklist\n        if os.name == 'nt':\n            # Use tasklist to check if PID exists\n            output = subprocess.check_output(f'tasklist /FI \"PID eq {pid}\"', shell=True).decode()\n            return str(pid) in output\n        else:\n            os.kill(pid, 0)\n            return True\n    except (OSError, subprocess.CalledProcessError):\n        return False\n\ndef start_bot():\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n            try:\n                pid = int(f.read().strip())\n                if is_running(pid):\n                    print(f\"Bot is already running (PID: {pid}).\")\n                    return\n                else:\n                    print(\"Found stale PID file. Cleaning up.\")\n            except ValueError:\n                print(\"Invalid PID file. Cleaning up.\")\n        \n        os.remove(PID_FILE)\n\n    print(\"Starting bot...\")\n    # Detached execution\n    if os.name == 'nt':\n        # Windows: specific flags to detach\n        process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [sys.executable, BOT_SCRIPT],\n            creationflags=subprocess.CREATE_NEW_CONSOLE,\n            cwd=os.getcwd()\n        )\n    else:\n        # Unix\n        process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [sys.executable, BOT_SCRIPT],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stdin=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            cwd=os.getcwd(),\n            start_new_session=True\n        )\n\n    with open(PID_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        f.write(str(process.pid))\n    \n    print(f\"Bot started with PID: {process.pid}\")\n\ndef stop_bot():\n    if not os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        print(\"Bot is not running (no PID file).\")\n        return\n\n    with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n        try:\n            pid = int(f.read().strip())\n        except ValueError:\n            print(\"Invalid PID file.\")\n            os.remove(PID_FILE)\n            return\n\n    if is_running(pid):\n        print(f\"Stopping bot (PID: {pid})...\")\n        try:\n            if os.name == 'nt':\n                subprocess.call(['taskkill', '/F', '/T', '/PID', str(pid)])\n            else:\n                os.kill(pid, signal.SIGTERM)\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Error stopping bot: {e}\")\n    else:\n        print(\"Bot process not found. Cleaning up PID file.\")\n\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        os.remove(PID_FILE)\n    print(\"Bot stopped.\")\n\ndef status_bot():\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n            try:\n                pid = int(f.read().strip())\n                if is_running(pid):\n                    print(f\"STATUS: ACTIVE (PID: {pid})\")\n                    return\n                else:\n                    print(\"STATUS: INACTIVE (Stale PID file found)\")\n            except ValueError:\n                print(\"STATUS: ERROR (Corrupted PID file)\")\n    else:\n        print(\"STATUS: INACTIVE\")\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Bot Control Interface\")\n    parser.add_argument('command', choices=['/start_bot', '/stop_bot', '/status'], help=\"Command to execute\")\n    \n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        parser.print_help()\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    if args.command == '/start_bot':\n        start_bot()\n    elif args.command == '/stop_bot':\n        stop_bot()\n    elif args.command == '/status':\n        status_bot()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n","file_path":"src/agent_wrapper.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":8374,"output":1496,"cacheRead":8078,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9870,"cost":{"input":0.016748,"output":0.017952,"cacheRead":0.0016156000000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.036315599999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771156861235}}
